1
00:00:00,933 --> 00:00:01,900
<i>We're already
carrying out the plan.</i>

2
00:00:01,900 --> 00:00:03,100
Is this what you're looking for?

3
00:00:03,100 --> 00:00:04,233
[METAL CREAKING, THUDS]

4
00:00:05,100 --> 00:00:06,267
<i> The map.</i>

5
00:00:06,267 --> 00:00:07,400
<i> This might be it.</i>

6
00:00:07,400 --> 00:00:08,500
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

7
00:00:08,500 --> 00:00:09,567
<i> Leon escaped.</i>

8
00:00:09,567 --> 00:00:10,867
<i> We need to find him.</i>

9
00:00:10,867 --> 00:00:14,033
<i>I believe now that you had
nothing to do with Juan's death.</i>

10
00:00:14,033 --> 00:00:15,000
<i> You should run now.</i>

11
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:16,233
<i> Leon escaped.</i>

12
00:00:16,233 --> 00:00:19,000
<i> If we don't find him,
</i>our entire plan will fall apart.

13
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:20,533
We need to speed up the search.

14
00:00:20,533 --> 00:00:22,667
<i>Time is running out,
especially for Leon.</i>

15
00:00:23,233 --> 00:00:25,433
<i> I didn't kill Juan.</i>

16
00:00:25,433 --> 00:00:28,033
<i> It's Uncle Andy and the
</i>police officer working with him.

17
00:00:28,033 --> 00:00:29,633
<i>They're the ones
who killed Juan!</i>

18
00:00:29,633 --> 00:00:31,600
<i>Juan's real killer
has been revealed.</i>

19
00:00:31,600 --> 00:00:33,300
<i> It's Marina De La Paz.</i>

20
00:00:33,300 --> 00:00:35,300
<i> There's a video
of her shooting Juan.</i>

21
00:00:35,333 --> 00:00:36,300
<i> You sold me out!</i>

22
00:00:36,300 --> 00:00:38,133
<i>I'm dragging your name
down with me!</i>

23
00:00:38,133 --> 00:00:39,267
<i> We're all going down together!</i>

24
00:00:41,767 --> 00:00:43,033
- [SCREAMS]
- [THUDS]

25
00:00:43,033 --> 00:00:44,167
[SCREAMS]

26
00:00:44,167 --> 00:00:45,133
- [GUN CLICKS]
- Aah!

27
00:00:45,133 --> 00:00:46,200
[GUNSHOTS]

28
00:00:47,433 --> 00:00:48,767
[GRUNTS]

29
00:00:48,767 --> 00:00:50,800
<i> You killed my son.</i>

30
00:00:50,800 --> 00:00:52,067
[GRUNTS]

31
00:00:57,767 --> 00:01:04,767
- [POLICE SIREN WAILING]
- [PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

32
00:01:17,767 --> 00:01:19,467
[HENRY] Who did this to you?

33
00:01:19,467 --> 00:01:26,300
- [POLICE SIREN WAILING]
- [PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

34
00:01:26,300 --> 00:01:33,267
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

35
00:02:27,833 --> 00:02:29,800
When Leon gets back,
do you think...

36
00:02:30,600 --> 00:02:32,233
we can tell them about us?

37
00:02:34,633 --> 00:02:35,933
I think...

38
00:02:38,100 --> 00:02:39,600
I think we can tell them now.

39
00:02:40,200 --> 00:02:41,233
Now?

40
00:02:42,600 --> 00:02:43,767
- [LUNA CHUCKLES]
- Are you sure?

41
00:02:44,700 --> 00:02:46,600
Well, everyone's already here.

42
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:48,000
So we can tell them all at once.

43
00:02:48,033 --> 00:02:50,133
I'll figure out the right timing
with Leon.

44
00:02:50,133 --> 00:02:53,633
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

45
00:02:53,633 --> 00:02:54,367
[LUNA CHUCKLES]

46
00:03:08,267 --> 00:03:13,333
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

47
00:03:13,333 --> 00:03:15,967
I still haven't
thanked you for...

48
00:03:15,967 --> 00:03:17,067
For what?

49
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:20,233
For helping me get down
from the tree.

50
00:03:20,233 --> 00:03:21,800
[SNICKERS]

51
00:03:21,833 --> 00:03:23,167
Of course I'd help you.

52
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:26,100
Sir, you and Sir Justin
could've just left me there

53
00:03:26,100 --> 00:03:28,767
and come back for me
after you visited the shrine.

54
00:03:28,767 --> 00:03:31,667
I wouldn't have felt right
leaving you behind

55
00:03:31,667 --> 00:03:32,867
while I was safe.

56
00:03:33,300 --> 00:03:34,300
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

57
00:03:34,900 --> 00:03:36,667
Thank you, Sir Martin.

58
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:39,167
[GASPS] And as a thank-you--

59
00:03:39,167 --> 00:03:40,800
[GROANS SLIGHTLY]
Don't tell me...

60
00:03:41,267 --> 00:03:42,633
A butterfly.

61
00:03:43,067 --> 00:03:44,100
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

62
00:03:45,100 --> 00:03:46,433
That's okay, Sari.

63
00:03:46,433 --> 00:03:47,967
Thanks for the butterfly.

64
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:50,133
- Hold it like this, sir.
- How?

65
00:03:50,133 --> 00:03:51,200
Like this.

66
00:03:52,067 --> 00:03:53,067
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

67
00:03:54,367 --> 00:03:55,800
So...

68
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:58,133
About that happy memory
you mentioned earlier...

69
00:03:59,833 --> 00:04:01,100
Hey, I meant that.

70
00:04:02,233 --> 00:04:04,733
I'm happy I got to know you
and Cheska.

71
00:04:07,833 --> 00:04:09,300
- Cheers, buddy.
- [BOTTLES CLINK]

72
00:04:10,067 --> 00:04:11,033
Buddy?

73
00:04:11,900 --> 00:04:13,067
Mh-mm.

74
00:04:13,067 --> 00:04:14,400
Don't you want us to be buddies?

75
00:04:14,967 --> 00:04:15,933
[SNICKERS]

76
00:04:16,900 --> 00:04:18,233
Is there really no chance...

77
00:04:18,833 --> 00:04:20,433
...for us to be
more than buddies?

78
00:04:20,433 --> 00:04:25,967
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

79
00:04:25,967 --> 00:04:26,967
[CHUCKLES AWKWARDLY]

80
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:28,333
Wow, you're getting bold, huh?

81
00:04:28,333 --> 00:04:31,400
Just because Juan's killer
has been caught.

82
00:04:33,967 --> 00:04:35,100
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]
Okay, fine.

83
00:04:35,500 --> 00:04:36,767
Let's just have a toast.

84
00:04:37,400 --> 00:04:38,433
- Cheers.
- [BOTTLES CLINK]

85
00:04:40,433 --> 00:04:45,300
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

86
00:04:45,300 --> 00:04:47,200
Cheska, let's have a toast!

87
00:04:50,300 --> 00:04:52,967
- [JUSTIN] So, again?
- [TRIXIE] Mh-mm.

88
00:04:52,967 --> 00:04:54,500
- [JUSTIN] Cheers.
- [TRIXIE] Cheers!

89
00:04:54,500 --> 00:04:56,033
- [BOTTLES CLINKING]
- [CHESKA] Cheers.

90
00:04:56,800 --> 00:04:58,000
Buddies?

91
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:59,033
Buddies.

92
00:04:59,467 --> 00:05:01,300
- Buddies?
- Buddies.

93
00:05:01,333 --> 00:05:02,900
[LAUGHING]

94
00:05:03,533 --> 00:05:05,833
- [LINE RINGING]
- [SIGHS]

95
00:05:07,300 --> 00:05:08,367
He's not answering?

96
00:05:09,333 --> 00:05:10,867
[LINE RINGING]

97
00:05:11,467 --> 00:05:12,967
Try calling him later.

98
00:05:12,967 --> 00:05:14,933
Edward might still be busy
at their hotel.

99
00:05:19,100 --> 00:05:20,100
Jade...

100
00:05:22,933 --> 00:05:26,033
I miss our happy memory.

101
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:30,167
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

102
00:05:30,167 --> 00:05:32,767
But now I know that there's...

103
00:05:34,367 --> 00:05:36,200
...someone else you want
to create happy memories with.

104
00:05:37,833 --> 00:05:40,033
If he's the one you want

105
00:05:40,033 --> 00:05:42,000
to share new
happy memories with...

106
00:05:43,267 --> 00:05:44,867
I won't stop you.

107
00:05:46,867 --> 00:05:48,400
What matters to me...

108
00:05:49,267 --> 00:05:50,267
...is that you're happy.

109
00:05:53,300 --> 00:05:54,400
Kiko...

110
00:05:54,400 --> 00:05:55,467
- What I was saying--
- Oh!

111
00:05:55,467 --> 00:05:56,567
Should we call Leon?

112
00:05:56,567 --> 00:06:02,367
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

113
00:06:02,367 --> 00:06:04,000
- [SIGHS]
- [TYPING]

114
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:06,200
[LINE RINGING]

115
00:06:06,500 --> 00:06:07,833
[FRIDA] Fred...

116
00:06:08,100 --> 00:06:10,800
[CHUCKLES] We'll get to be
with Leon again.

117
00:06:12,500 --> 00:06:15,000
He won't have
to hide anymore. [SNIFFLES]

118
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:17,067
He won't go to prison anymore.

119
00:06:17,500 --> 00:06:19,300
[SOBBING, EXHALES]

120
00:06:20,567 --> 00:06:24,900
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

121
00:06:24,900 --> 00:06:26,300
[WIND WHISTLING]

122
00:06:26,300 --> 00:06:27,333
[PICTURE FRAME THUDS]

123
00:06:27,333 --> 00:06:34,333
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [BREATHES HEAVILY]

124
00:06:49,200 --> 00:06:54,500
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

125
00:06:54,500 --> 00:06:58,133
[CHAINS RATTLING]

126
00:07:05,033 --> 00:07:06,033
[SOBS QUIETLY]

127
00:07:08,167 --> 00:07:10,200
[LEON PANTING]

128
00:07:10,200 --> 00:07:12,500
[CHAINS RATTLING]

129
00:07:12,500 --> 00:07:14,233
[LEON SCREAMS] Coward!

130
00:07:14,267 --> 00:07:21,267
- [TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [CHAINS RATTLING]

131
00:07:22,467 --> 00:07:23,900
Help!

132
00:07:24,633 --> 00:07:27,533
[CHAINS RATTLING]

133
00:07:28,333 --> 00:07:29,633
Help!

134
00:07:30,300 --> 00:07:31,600
[LEON SHOUTS IN THE DISTANCE]
Help!

135
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:34,067
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

136
00:07:34,067 --> 00:07:35,133
What's that?

137
00:07:44,067 --> 00:07:46,700
- [UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]
- [MUFFLED VOICES]

138
00:07:46,700 --> 00:07:47,667
Monette!

139
00:07:48,333 --> 00:07:49,533
Raphie, my god!

140
00:07:50,267 --> 00:07:52,067
- You're so dramatic.
- You scared me.

141
00:07:52,067 --> 00:07:53,767
Why did you do that?
You scared me!

142
00:07:54,667 --> 00:07:56,467
I just wanted to hug you.

143
00:07:57,767 --> 00:08:00,167
I've been hearing voices
for a while.

144
00:08:00,167 --> 00:08:01,267
What is it?

145
00:08:01,267 --> 00:08:02,667
It's been going-- Listen to it.

146
00:08:09,233 --> 00:08:10,400
There, don't you hear it?

147
00:08:10,833 --> 00:08:12,467
I'm getting goosebumps.

148
00:08:12,467 --> 00:08:14,700
[RAPHIE VOCALIZING OFF-KEY]

149
00:08:14,700 --> 00:08:15,800
There it is.

150
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:23,633
Oh, Raphie! It was just you!

151
00:08:24,133 --> 00:08:25,233
It was just you!

152
00:08:25,233 --> 00:08:26,867
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

153
00:08:26,867 --> 00:08:28,333
[EXHALES]

154
00:08:28,333 --> 00:08:30,667
Why were you vocalizing anyway?
And you're doing it wrong.

155
00:08:30,667 --> 00:08:32,433
Oh. Show me then.

156
00:08:33,167 --> 00:08:34,200
Listen up.

157
00:08:34,200 --> 00:08:35,800
I've taught you this before.

158
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:44,567
[MONETTE VOCALIZING]

159
00:08:50,400 --> 00:08:51,533
[STOPS VOCALIZING]

160
00:08:57,267 --> 00:08:59,500
This is why I don't want you
joining karaoke nights.

161
00:08:59,833 --> 00:09:01,733
I can't compete with your voice.

162
00:09:02,467 --> 00:09:04,433
Remember,
once you study in Manila,

163
00:09:04,833 --> 00:09:06,533
I'll sing karaoke
whenever I want.

164
00:09:07,867 --> 00:09:08,867
[EXHALES]

165
00:09:10,633 --> 00:09:12,433
- Hmm.
- Thank you, Monette.

166
00:09:14,733 --> 00:09:18,333
Thank you for not giving up
on my dream.

167
00:09:20,267 --> 00:09:22,200
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

168
00:09:22,567 --> 00:09:24,467
I promise,
I'll do my best there.

169
00:09:25,167 --> 00:09:27,567
And when I become
a famous designer,

170
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:32,800
oh, I'll make you the most
beautiful wedding gown!

171
00:09:32,800 --> 00:09:34,167
- Really, huh?
- Oh.

172
00:09:34,867 --> 00:09:35,900
Then...

173
00:09:36,633 --> 00:09:38,767
we'll put some pearls here.

174
00:09:40,467 --> 00:09:42,533
Why does it have to be
a wedding gown?

175
00:09:42,533 --> 00:09:44,567
Of course,
I'd want a debutant gown first.

176
00:09:44,567 --> 00:09:46,267
I didn't have an
18th birthday party, remember?

177
00:09:46,267 --> 00:09:47,433
[CHUCKLES] Fine, let's do it.

178
00:09:47,433 --> 00:09:49,800
Let's make the debutant party
of a 30-year-old happen.

179
00:09:49,800 --> 00:09:51,167
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

180
00:09:51,167 --> 00:09:52,367
Come here.

181
00:09:53,400 --> 00:09:54,833
I love you, Monette.

182
00:09:54,833 --> 00:09:56,433
I love you, sis.

183
00:09:56,433 --> 00:09:58,500
I love you so much!

184
00:09:58,500 --> 00:09:59,833
- Really? For real?
- Mm-hmm.

185
00:09:59,833 --> 00:10:01,667
- You love me?
- Of course.

186
00:10:01,700 --> 00:10:03,900
Okay, then get back to work.

187
00:10:04,533 --> 00:10:06,600
- Come on. You love me, right?
- Right now?

188
00:10:09,633 --> 00:10:10,667
I'm here.

189
00:10:11,300 --> 00:10:15,433
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

190
00:10:15,433 --> 00:10:16,833
Just wait for my call.

191
00:10:27,433 --> 00:10:28,800
<i> Who killed Marina?</i>

192
00:10:30,633 --> 00:10:32,167
<i> Do I have any other enemies?</i>

193
00:10:37,433 --> 00:10:44,367
[MUSIC TURNS TENSE]

194
00:10:49,900 --> 00:10:51,800
I guess now is the time
to tell them.

195
00:10:53,767 --> 00:10:54,967
[CHESKA] Bro!

196
00:10:54,967 --> 00:10:56,200
Brothers!

197
00:10:56,633 --> 00:10:57,600
- Oh.
- Bro.

198
00:10:57,967 --> 00:10:59,400
Cheska, what is it?

199
00:10:59,400 --> 00:11:00,900
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

200
00:11:00,900 --> 00:11:02,300
The cop
is all over social media.

201
00:11:02,733 --> 00:11:04,267
- [KIKO] Who?
- Huh?

202
00:11:04,267 --> 00:11:06,733
The cop Syvera was
talking about earlier.

203
00:11:06,733 --> 00:11:08,300
The one who killed Juan.

204
00:11:08,733 --> 00:11:09,833
Dela Paz?

205
00:11:12,800 --> 00:11:14,767
Yes, she's dead.

206
00:11:14,767 --> 00:11:15,767
- What?
- What?

207
00:11:17,333 --> 00:11:18,333
[CHESKA] Look.

208
00:11:18,967 --> 00:11:20,800
They just found her dead.

209
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:23,200
If Dela Paz is dead,

210
00:11:23,200 --> 00:11:24,567
then who can help us
reveal Andy's crimes?

211
00:11:24,567 --> 00:11:26,300
Let's not lose hope.

212
00:11:26,633 --> 00:11:28,967
We can still clear Leon's name,
because there's video evidence.

213
00:11:28,967 --> 00:11:31,267
But the... treasure.

214
00:11:31,900 --> 00:11:34,467
And the truth
about our fathers' death.

215
00:11:35,500 --> 00:11:36,567
You know what?

216
00:11:36,567 --> 00:11:38,700
I wouldn't be surprised
if Andy did that to her.

217
00:11:38,700 --> 00:11:39,933
[JADE] Oh god.

218
00:11:39,933 --> 00:11:41,733
What is happening to this place?

219
00:11:43,967 --> 00:11:45,533
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

220
00:11:47,067 --> 00:11:54,033
- [FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

221
00:12:02,367 --> 00:12:04,367
[ANDY] Sandro, show yourself.

222
00:12:09,467 --> 00:12:11,033
Face me, Andy.

223
00:12:14,800 --> 00:12:16,500
Andy, let's talk!

224
00:12:19,333 --> 00:12:21,500
You killed my son.

225
00:12:22,533 --> 00:12:23,967
You and that cop.

226
00:12:24,667 --> 00:12:26,000
[ANDY] I didn't do it.

227
00:12:26,800 --> 00:12:27,867
It was Marina.

228
00:12:28,367 --> 00:12:29,267
I wasn't in the video

229
00:12:29,267 --> 00:12:31,033
because I had nothing
to do with it.

230
00:12:32,700 --> 00:12:34,033
Believe me.

231
00:12:34,600 --> 00:12:36,033
We're on each other's side,
remember?

232
00:12:36,667 --> 00:12:39,667
We thought of burning down
Hotel 88 before, remember?

233
00:12:40,400 --> 00:12:42,900
But I was the only one who
took the fall from those two.

234
00:12:44,500 --> 00:12:46,567
You weren't there
when I was being killed.

235
00:12:47,333 --> 00:12:49,800
[ANDY] But you ended up
killing them, didn't you?

236
00:12:49,833 --> 00:12:54,867
[MUSIC TURNS GRIM]

237
00:12:55,567 --> 00:12:56,967
I still can't believe it.

238
00:12:57,700 --> 00:13:00,833
Sir Henri just told us,
then hours later she's dead.

239
00:13:01,433 --> 00:13:03,067
No one else would do that
but Andy.

240
00:13:03,867 --> 00:13:06,433
He has the money and the people
to make it happen.

241
00:13:06,433 --> 00:13:07,867
And that's
what's pissing me off.

242
00:13:07,867 --> 00:13:09,433
He had Dela Paz killed

243
00:13:09,433 --> 00:13:11,367
so she wouldn't be able
to speak against him.

244
00:13:11,367 --> 00:13:13,667
- [SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]
- [MARTIN SIGHS EXASPERATEDLY]

245
00:13:13,667 --> 00:13:16,467
Andy might be free now but
soon the truth will come out.

246
00:13:17,400 --> 00:13:18,900
He will pay
for everything he has done.

247
00:13:21,567 --> 00:13:24,400
I won't trust you anymore, Andy.

248
00:13:28,167 --> 00:13:35,133
[MUSIC TURNS SUSPENSEFUL]

249
00:13:50,400 --> 00:13:54,767
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

250
00:13:55,467 --> 00:13:56,533
Andy.

251
00:13:57,567 --> 00:13:58,800
Come out here.

252
00:14:00,100 --> 00:14:01,400
Let's talk.

253
00:14:02,967 --> 00:14:04,000
Andy.

254
00:14:11,800 --> 00:14:12,900
- [BLOW LANDS]
- [ANDY GRUNTS] Argh!

255
00:14:12,900 --> 00:14:14,667
[SANDRO GROANING] Agh!

256
00:14:15,633 --> 00:14:17,633
- [FOOTSTEPS RETREATING]
- [OBJECTS FALLING]

257
00:14:17,633 --> 00:14:21,667
[SANDRO GROANING,
BREATHING HEAVILY]

258
00:14:28,167 --> 00:14:30,567
[LINE RINGING]

259
00:14:31,767 --> 00:14:38,700
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

260
00:14:43,767 --> 00:14:45,067
[EXHALES LOUDLY]

261
00:14:47,067 --> 00:14:50,000
I want more men
watching over the house.

262
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:53,233
Then, whoever's assigned
to watch the CCTV,

263
00:14:53,233 --> 00:14:54,433
tell them to focus on it.

264
00:14:54,433 --> 00:14:57,600
They need to keep an eye
on anyone who enters the house.

265
00:14:58,000 --> 00:14:59,467
- Okay?
- Yes, boss.

266
00:14:59,467 --> 00:15:01,633
- Alright, tell the others.
- Let's go.

267
00:15:08,667 --> 00:15:10,200
- [INHALES]
- Dad...

268
00:15:10,200 --> 00:15:11,733
- [EXHALES]
- What does this all mean?

269
00:15:12,233 --> 00:15:13,633
I'm glad you're home.

270
00:15:13,633 --> 00:15:14,567
No.

271
00:15:15,433 --> 00:15:16,733
I'm not here to stay.

272
00:15:18,367 --> 00:15:19,733
What does this all mean?

273
00:15:20,300 --> 00:15:22,500
Why did you send men to my pad?

274
00:15:23,067 --> 00:15:26,033
It's for our protection.
It's for<i> your</i> protection.

275
00:15:28,067 --> 00:15:29,600
I'm safer without you.

276
00:15:30,500 --> 00:15:33,067
- If you don't tell me--
- Enough!

277
00:15:34,400 --> 00:15:37,267
Can you please
stop accusing me?

278
00:15:37,500 --> 00:15:39,500
You don't understand

279
00:15:39,500 --> 00:15:42,200
what kind of danger
we're facing right now.

280
00:15:42,600 --> 00:15:43,633
Okay!

281
00:15:44,167 --> 00:15:45,300
Alright, then.

282
00:15:46,167 --> 00:15:47,633
What kind of danger is it?

283
00:15:48,333 --> 00:15:49,500
I'm all ears.

284
00:15:49,767 --> 00:15:51,733
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYS]

285
00:15:52,767 --> 00:15:55,100
Just when he could go home,

286
00:15:55,100 --> 00:15:57,500
that's when
we couldn't reach him.

287
00:15:58,600 --> 00:15:59,600
Mom.

288
00:16:00,267 --> 00:16:02,300
Maybe Leon
wants to surprise us.

289
00:16:02,767 --> 00:16:05,667
I'm sure he's seen all of our
missed calls and messages.

290
00:16:06,567 --> 00:16:07,733
Or maybe...

291
00:16:08,533 --> 00:16:09,767
Maybe he's here.

292
00:16:10,800 --> 00:16:17,733
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

293
00:16:18,867 --> 00:16:20,367
Still nothing?

294
00:16:26,100 --> 00:16:27,233
I hope...

295
00:16:30,167 --> 00:16:31,333
[SIGHS]

296
00:16:31,333 --> 00:16:33,733
I hope he comes home.

297
00:16:34,800 --> 00:16:36,833
I hope Leon comes home.

298
00:16:37,767 --> 00:16:44,733
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

299
00:16:48,700 --> 00:16:49,733
Stay here.

300
00:16:50,367 --> 00:16:52,200
I'll have your stuff
taken back here.

301
00:16:52,200 --> 00:16:53,867
- You're not leaving.
- No.

302
00:16:55,267 --> 00:16:56,533
I know what it is.

303
00:16:59,433 --> 00:17:00,800
I'm just waiting

304
00:17:01,433 --> 00:17:03,667
for you to tell me yourself.

305
00:17:03,867 --> 00:17:06,767
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

306
00:17:07,533 --> 00:17:09,367
Is it about the cop?

307
00:17:09,733 --> 00:17:10,833
De La Paz, right?

308
00:17:12,533 --> 00:17:14,767
The cop you either killed
or got killed

309
00:17:17,567 --> 00:17:20,400
to keep her silent
about what she knew.

310
00:17:21,267 --> 00:17:23,500
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

311
00:17:23,500 --> 00:17:24,700
And now...

312
00:17:25,767 --> 00:17:27,533
Now, you're panicking.

313
00:17:28,200 --> 00:17:29,900
Okay. Fine.

314
00:17:29,900 --> 00:17:32,233
Since you know everything,

315
00:17:32,233 --> 00:17:34,800
you've probably also
know about De La Paz's video

316
00:17:34,800 --> 00:17:38,600
where she explicitly says
she killed Juan.

317
00:17:38,600 --> 00:17:40,233
Just like you told her to.

318
00:17:41,333 --> 00:17:44,133
[INHALES SHARPLY]
My gosh, Edward!

319
00:17:45,200 --> 00:17:46,233
[SCOFFS]

320
00:17:46,433 --> 00:17:48,600
Get all of your men
out of my pad.

321
00:17:48,633 --> 00:17:51,233
I don't need protection
from anything!

322
00:17:51,833 --> 00:17:57,800
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

323
00:17:58,567 --> 00:17:59,967
- [MONETTE] How many years?
- [RAPHIE] Is that all?

324
00:17:59,967 --> 00:18:01,800
- [MONETTE] Is he cute?
- [RAPHIE] Okay!

325
00:18:02,267 --> 00:18:04,200
Copy, ma'am. We're on it.

326
00:18:04,200 --> 00:18:05,533
- [NATALIE] And he's so...
- Monette.

327
00:18:05,533 --> 00:18:07,333
- [GIGGLES]
- Monette!

328
00:18:07,667 --> 00:18:08,600
My god!

329
00:18:09,233 --> 00:18:10,600
What is it, Raphie?

330
00:18:10,600 --> 00:18:12,300
I'm still catching up
with Natalie.

331
00:18:12,300 --> 00:18:14,633
Room 304 wants room service.

332
00:18:14,633 --> 00:18:16,633
- Wait up.
- Fresh fruits platter.

333
00:18:16,933 --> 00:18:19,300
- It's the last order, right?
- Mm-hm.

334
00:18:19,300 --> 00:18:20,633
Alright, I'll do it.

335
00:18:20,633 --> 00:18:23,667
But help Cesar
with the garbage, okay?

336
00:18:23,700 --> 00:18:24,800
[EXHALES LOUDLY]

337
00:18:25,367 --> 00:18:27,233
Don't scoff in front of me.

338
00:18:27,233 --> 00:18:28,800
This is the only thing
I'm never gonna miss.

339
00:18:28,800 --> 00:18:30,267
Garbage duties.

340
00:18:30,267 --> 00:18:31,967
Oh, you little...

341
00:18:32,600 --> 00:18:33,667
There we go.

342
00:18:34,633 --> 00:18:35,767
[HUMMING]

343
00:18:41,433 --> 00:18:43,367
Room service!

344
00:18:43,367 --> 00:18:45,400
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

345
00:18:45,400 --> 00:18:47,267
Hello. Good evening, ma'am.

346
00:18:47,267 --> 00:18:48,700
- Good evening.
- Here's your order.

347
00:18:48,700 --> 00:18:50,633
- Please put it here.
- Okay.

348
00:18:50,867 --> 00:18:53,233
Should we charge this
to your room, ma'am?

349
00:18:53,233 --> 00:18:54,300
Ah, yes, please.

350
00:18:54,300 --> 00:18:57,433
Also, why isn't the water
working in the bathroom?

351
00:18:57,467 --> 00:18:58,533
Ah...

352
00:18:58,533 --> 00:19:00,867
It was working fine earlier,
but now, it's not.

353
00:19:00,867 --> 00:19:03,633
Oh, okay. Let me check first.

354
00:19:04,833 --> 00:19:11,800
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

355
00:19:14,800 --> 00:19:16,233
Oh, dear.

356
00:19:16,967 --> 00:19:20,800
Now, I have to check
the basement myself.

357
00:19:21,867 --> 00:19:23,000
Mm-hm!

358
00:19:25,767 --> 00:19:32,700
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

359
00:19:47,700 --> 00:19:51,667
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

360
00:19:52,633 --> 00:19:53,833
[MONETTE] Goodness!

361
00:19:53,833 --> 00:19:56,633
Why do we always have
water problems?

362
00:19:57,600 --> 00:19:59,667
How can I fix this now?

363
00:20:01,600 --> 00:20:02,700
[WATER DRIPPING]

364
00:20:03,633 --> 00:20:10,567
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

365
00:20:15,100 --> 00:20:16,300
Hello...

366
00:20:18,067 --> 00:20:19,333
Hello?

367
00:20:27,767 --> 00:20:29,100
[CHAIN RATTLING]

368
00:20:29,100 --> 00:20:30,567
Raphie?

369
00:20:35,667 --> 00:20:36,800
[LEON] Help!

370
00:20:39,733 --> 00:20:40,900
Is someone there?

371
00:20:43,667 --> 00:20:44,800
Help!

372
00:20:47,733 --> 00:20:49,667
Raphie, stop messing with me!

373
00:20:50,467 --> 00:20:55,467
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

374
00:20:55,733 --> 00:20:57,100
[CHAIN RATTLES]

375
00:21:02,400 --> 00:21:03,867
Help me!

376
00:21:07,600 --> 00:21:08,700
Who's there?

377
00:21:09,533 --> 00:21:11,500
Raphie, I swear to god.

378
00:21:12,100 --> 00:21:13,533
Help!

379
00:21:17,133 --> 00:21:18,600
Help me!

380
00:21:22,900 --> 00:21:24,000
Raphie?

381
00:21:31,700 --> 00:21:32,900
[LEON] Help!

382
00:21:35,900 --> 00:21:36,933
[RATTLES]

383
00:21:38,433 --> 00:21:39,667
Help!

384
00:21:44,100 --> 00:21:45,567
Help me!

385
00:21:45,767 --> 00:21:46,900
"Help me"?

386
00:21:47,100 --> 00:21:48,967
[RATTLING]

387
00:21:51,133 --> 00:21:52,133
[GRUNTS]

388
00:21:53,467 --> 00:21:54,633
Help!

389
00:21:56,033 --> 00:21:57,767
Help me!

390
00:22:00,867 --> 00:22:03,133
- [GRUNTS]
- [SHUFFLES]

391
00:22:03,733 --> 00:22:04,733
[GASPS]

392
00:22:07,433 --> 00:22:09,200
[CHAINS RATTLING]

393
00:22:09,200 --> 00:22:10,233
[LEON GRUNTS]

394
00:22:11,333 --> 00:22:12,667
Help!

395
00:22:13,667 --> 00:22:15,633
- [GRUNTS]
- [WOOD CREAKS]

396
00:22:18,767 --> 00:22:21,167
- [GRUNTS]
- [SLIDES OPEN]

397
00:22:21,733 --> 00:22:23,100
[EXCLAIMS]

398
00:22:25,167 --> 00:22:26,533
What is this?

399
00:22:29,367 --> 00:22:31,433
- [LEON]<i> I'm down here!
</i>- [CHAINS RATTLE]

400
00:22:31,433 --> 00:22:33,333
<i> I'm down here!</i>

401
00:22:33,333 --> 00:22:35,000
[GASPS] Who was that?

402
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:40,200
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

403
00:22:40,200 --> 00:22:41,333
What is this place?

404
00:22:41,333 --> 00:22:48,333
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

405
00:22:48,600 --> 00:22:50,100
Help!

406
00:22:51,733 --> 00:22:52,767
[WHISPERS] Oh my god.

407
00:22:56,033 --> 00:22:57,300
Huh?

408
00:22:57,300 --> 00:22:58,767
- Monette?
- Leon?

409
00:22:58,767 --> 00:23:01,767
- Monette, help me!
- [CHAINS RATTLE]

410
00:23:01,767 --> 00:23:03,800
- Help me!
- Leon!

411
00:23:03,800 --> 00:23:04,800
Monette.

412
00:23:04,800 --> 00:23:06,700
Dear god,
what happened to you?!

413
00:23:06,700 --> 00:23:08,667
- [LEON GROANS IN PAIN]
- Who did this?

414
00:23:08,667 --> 00:23:10,333
What happened, Leon?!

415
00:23:10,333 --> 00:23:17,267
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

416
00:23:25,733 --> 00:23:28,633
- Help me.
- We've been looking for you!

417
00:23:28,633 --> 00:23:31,100
The police said
you never came home!

418
00:23:31,100 --> 00:23:32,567
Free me, Monette.

419
00:23:32,567 --> 00:23:39,500
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

420
00:23:41,100 --> 00:23:42,233
[CHAINS RATTLE]

421
00:23:42,233 --> 00:23:43,333
How do I free you?

422
00:23:44,700 --> 00:23:47,033
- What do I do?
- [CHAINS RATTLE]

423
00:23:47,600 --> 00:23:50,600
[PANICKED BREATHING]

424
00:23:50,600 --> 00:23:51,700
How?

425
00:23:52,433 --> 00:23:54,767
Leon, I'll go back up.

426
00:23:54,800 --> 00:23:56,267
I'm going to ask for help.

427
00:23:56,267 --> 00:23:57,867
No, he might come back.

428
00:23:57,867 --> 00:23:59,733
I'll be quick.
I promise.

429
00:23:59,733 --> 00:24:00,867
- Wait here.
- Hey.

430
00:24:00,867 --> 00:24:04,267
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

431
00:24:04,267 --> 00:24:07,267
You need to
get out of here, Monette.

432
00:24:07,267 --> 00:24:09,167
- Run!
- You did this?

433
00:24:09,167 --> 00:24:11,467
You abducted Leon?

434
00:24:11,467 --> 00:24:12,867
Did you do this to him?

435
00:24:12,867 --> 00:24:14,700
Monette, get out of here!

436
00:24:14,700 --> 00:24:16,367
You're a monster.

437
00:24:16,367 --> 00:24:18,633
- Monette!
- Let him go!

438
00:24:18,633 --> 00:24:20,367
Let Leon go!

439
00:24:20,367 --> 00:24:21,733
Give me the key!

440
00:24:21,733 --> 00:24:23,167
- Let him go!
- Monette, stop!

441
00:24:23,167 --> 00:24:25,767
- Monette!
- Why are you doing this?

442
00:24:25,767 --> 00:24:27,200
Get out of here, Monette!

443
00:24:27,200 --> 00:24:28,400
Let him go!

444
00:24:28,400 --> 00:24:30,767
- [MONETTE SCREAMS]
- No!

445
00:24:30,800 --> 00:24:32,600
No! Don't!

446
00:24:32,600 --> 00:24:34,233
- [METAL CLANKING]
- [MONETTE GRUNTS]

447
00:24:34,233 --> 00:24:35,500
[SHOUTS]

448
00:24:35,500 --> 00:24:36,867
- Monette!
- [BONE CRACKING]

449
00:24:36,867 --> 00:24:38,833
- [SANDRO GRUNTING]
- Monette!

450
00:24:38,833 --> 00:24:40,900
- [BLOWS LANDING]
- [FLESH SQUELCHING]

451
00:24:40,900 --> 00:24:42,533
Stop!

452
00:24:42,533 --> 00:24:44,200
- [CRYING]
- [FLESH SQUELCHING]

453
00:24:44,200 --> 00:24:45,433
- [BLOW LANDS]
- [BONE CRACKS]

454
00:24:47,467 --> 00:24:48,467
[BODY THUDS]

455
00:24:48,467 --> 00:24:51,367
[SOBS] Monette!

456
00:24:51,367 --> 00:24:53,500
Monette!

457
00:24:53,500 --> 00:24:56,133
[SOBBING] Monette...

458
00:24:56,133 --> 00:24:57,767
No.

459
00:24:57,767 --> 00:24:59,667
Monette!

460
00:24:59,667 --> 00:25:03,767
[SOBBING]

461
00:25:03,800 --> 00:25:05,533
Monette!

462
00:25:05,533 --> 00:25:09,700
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

463
00:25:09,700 --> 00:25:11,167
No...

464
00:25:11,167 --> 00:25:16,167
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

465
00:25:16,167 --> 00:25:17,700
Monette!

466
00:25:18,433 --> 00:25:21,367
<i> Reveal what is concealed.</i>

467
00:25:21,367 --> 00:25:23,567
<i> Reach what lies hidden.</i>

468
00:25:23,567 --> 00:25:27,700
<i>Guide the eyes
of those in search.</i>

469
00:25:27,700 --> 00:25:29,933
<i>Things are missing
from my house.</i>

470
00:25:29,933 --> 00:25:32,467
<i> Leave my family alone.</i>

471
00:25:32,467 --> 00:25:34,300
<i>They have nothing
to do with this.</i>

472
00:25:34,300 --> 00:25:35,767
[CRYING]

473
00:25:35,800 --> 00:25:38,433
<i> I will make things right.</i>

474
00:25:39,667 --> 00:25:41,200
[SCREAMS]

475
00:25:41,200 --> 00:25:42,167
<i> Help!</i>

476
00:25:43,200 --> 00:25:45,700
<i> Listen to your heart.</i>

477
00:25:45,700 --> 00:25:47,233
<i> It knows the truth.</i>
